It's lost its nutritional value.

00:12:40.820 --> 00:12:44.700
Instead, you buy the seeds, you buy the wheat.

00:12:44.700 --> 00:12:45.580
And mill it yourself.

00:12:45.580 --> 00:12:46.780
You can mill it yourself

00:12:46.780 --> 00:12:50.040
and that's instant nutrition in real bread.

00:12:50.040 --> 00:12:52.480
Okay, I think I've got the concept.

00:12:52.480 --> 00:12:55.280
Tell me about Haiti and Tanzania.

00:12:55.280 --> 00:12:57.520
You've turned this into a missionary enterprise.

00:12:57.520 --> 00:13:02.300
Yes, so in 2007, after traveling and speaking

00:13:02.300 --> 00:13:04.920
on the nutritional benefits and having thousands

00:13:04.920 --> 00:13:07.240
of testimonies of people coming to me and saying,

00:13:07.240 --> 00:13:08.860
it's the bread, that's all I changed,

00:13:08.860 --> 00:13:10.900
and this, this, my cholesterol dropped,

00:13:10.900 --> 00:13:13.880
my blood sugar stabilized, irritable bowel, completely

00:13:13.880 --> 00:13:14.400
gone,

00:13:14.400 --> 00:13:16.960
I started going, I gotta get this into the hands

00:13:16.960 --> 00:13:19.360
of people that truly can't afford it.

00:13:19.360 --> 00:13:21.520
Some of us will say, I can't afford it, I don't have

00:13:21.520 --> 00:13:21.880
time.

00:13:21.880 --> 00:13:24.160
Most people do, but some truly can't.

00:13:24.160 --> 00:13:28.300
So in 2007, I started a ministry called Real Bread Outreach

00:13:28.300 --> 00:13:31.200
to get grain mills and grain into the hands of those

00:13:31.200 --> 00:13:34.040
that would take the time to mill the flour.

00:13:34.040 --> 00:13:37.360
Their lives changed, their health changed, and so--

00:13:37.360 --> 00:13:40.480
Tell us about the starving school children in Haiti.

00:13:40.480 --> 00:13:41.460
Yep, so--

00:13:41.460 --> 00:13:42.800
You have been there 15 times.

00:13:42.800 --> 00:13:46.260
Yes, so in 2007, that's when I started the ministry.

00:13:46.260 --> 00:13:49.420
2016, I was asked to come to Haiti.

00:13:49.420 --> 00:13:52.620
Pastor Jumi Septembre, that's here with me this weekend,

00:13:52.620 --> 00:13:56.060
he reached out to me and said,

00:13:56.060 --> 00:13:58.100
I have starving school children.

00:13:58.100 --> 00:14:00.740
I can't afford to feed them a meal,

00:14:00.740 --> 00:14:02.980
but I've heard your teaching on the nutritional

00:14:02.980 --> 00:14:03.700
benefits

00:14:03.700 --> 00:14:05.300
of the whole grain.

00:14:05.300 --> 00:14:08.540
All but four nutrients that we need to sustain life

00:14:08.540 --> 00:14:10.420
and health are in wheat.

00:14:10.420 --> 00:14:13.520
Wow, he said, so I can mill this flour, make some bread,

00:14:13.520 --> 00:14:15.300
give these school children a roll.

00:14:15.300 --> 00:14:17.140
That might be the most nutrient-dense thing

00:14:17.140 --> 00:14:18.260
they get all day.

00:14:18.260 --> 00:14:21.180
So I made my first trip in 2016.

00:14:21.180 --> 00:14:24.920
I did 15 trips over the course of the next couple of

00:14:24.920 --> 00:14:25.300
years,

00:14:25.300 --> 00:14:28.560
training a group of young men that lived

00:14:28.560 --> 00:14:30.860
in the first orphanage where I worked with,

00:14:30.860 --> 00:14:34.730
and they were making bread to feed the 500 school

00:14:34.730 --> 00:14:35.260
children

00:14:35.260 --> 00:14:37.820
and the 150 orphans that lived there.

00:14:37.820 --> 00:14:40.140
And they were getting up before school

00:14:40.140 --> 00:14:42.900
and making all this bread, and it was a real blessing.

00:14:42.900 --> 00:14:45.420
How many thousands of children have been fed?

00:14:45.420 --> 00:14:49.260
Oh, golly, I don't know, thousands every year.

00:14:49.260 --> 00:14:50.100
I mean--

00:14:50.100 --> 00:14:52.460
This reminds me of when Jesus was on the hillside.

00:14:52.460 --> 00:14:53.380
Yep. Right?

00:14:53.380 --> 00:14:55.980
He took how many, five loaves and two fishes?

00:14:55.980 --> 00:14:57.680
Five loaves and two fishes, yeah.

00:14:57.680 --> 00:15:01.420
And he multiplied to thousands of people were eating.

00:15:01.420 --> 00:15:02.260
Yeah.

00:15:02.260 --> 00:15:03.420
That's what Sue Becker is doing.

00:15:03.420 --> 00:15:04.260
Yeah.

