Yes, first trip was in 2011.

00:19:33.900 --> 00:19:35.580
And on the trip over there,

00:19:35.580 --> 00:19:37.700
we were doing women's conferences,

00:19:37.700 --> 00:19:39.340
some discipleship training.

00:19:39.340 --> 00:19:42.880
And I was there at the time with my girlfriend,

00:19:42.880 --> 00:19:45.380
and just felt the Holy Spirit come over me

00:19:45.380 --> 00:19:47.260
and asked her to marry me.

00:19:47.260 --> 00:19:48.180
Proposed to her.

00:19:48.180 --> 00:19:50.320
Proposed to her on a train in India.

00:19:50.320 --> 00:19:52.260
And then we adopted two children from there as well

00:19:52.260 --> 00:19:53.900
because of the friendships we've cultivated

00:19:53.900 --> 00:19:56.060
and God really shaped our heart for India.

00:19:56.060 --> 00:19:58.770
So that's a big responsibility of our life is through

00:19:58.770 --> 00:19:58.980
India.

00:19:58.980 --> 00:20:02.070
So now you're a spokesman for this international

00:20:02.070 --> 00:20:02.580
ministry

00:20:02.580 --> 00:20:05.380
by Victor John,

00:20:05.380 --> 00:20:10.260
and it's called Asian Partners International Inc,

00:20:10.260 --> 00:20:12.460
apii.org.

00:20:12.460 --> 00:20:13.420
What is that?

00:20:13.420 --> 00:20:16.060
Yes, so Victor's actually just a friend of the ministry,

00:20:16.060 --> 00:20:19.420
but APII is a movement that we've done

00:20:19.420 --> 00:20:23.130
where we work with people in the northern parts of

00:20:23.130 --> 00:20:23.620
India,

00:20:23.620 --> 00:20:26.420
where it's just a discipleship making movement.

00:20:26.420 --> 00:20:28.660
It's primarily focused through meeting the needs

00:20:28.660 --> 00:20:30.100
of a community first.

00:20:30.100 --> 00:20:32.500
So the Luke 10 model, going in there,

00:20:32.500 --> 00:20:34.980
finding out where the needs are, meeting those needs,

00:20:34.980 --> 00:20:37.900
whether that's through women empowerment,

00:20:37.900 --> 00:20:39.560
teaching them about microfinance loans,

00:20:39.560 --> 00:20:41.360
training them up that way,

00:20:41.360 --> 00:20:43.150
meeting the needs of children who don't have any

00:20:43.150 --> 00:20:43.720
education,

00:20:43.720 --> 00:20:45.760
getting kids off the railway stations,

00:20:45.760 --> 00:20:47.660
and then meeting the needs of those families,

00:20:47.660 --> 00:20:48.500
bringing them in,

00:20:48.500 --> 00:20:50.200
and they find out about the love of Christ,

00:20:50.200 --> 00:20:51.960
which is the whole reason that we're there.

00:20:51.960 --> 00:20:54.920
And then through that, house fellowships get cultivated,

00:20:54.920 --> 00:20:56.860
people get to come to know the name of Jesus,

00:20:56.860 --> 00:20:59.800
and this has been going on since 1997.

00:20:59.800 --> 00:21:04.440
So 1997, that's like 25 years now, almost 30 years.

00:21:04.440 --> 00:21:06.580
Yeah, just about 30 years and a couple of years here.

00:21:06.580 --> 00:21:07.640
That's incredible.

00:21:07.640 --> 00:21:10.960
So you have been how many times?

00:21:10.960 --> 00:21:13.520
So I have been between the adoptions

00:21:13.520 --> 00:21:15.860
and the trips over there, I've been five times.

00:21:15.860 --> 00:21:16.860
Five times? Yeah.

00:21:16.860 --> 00:21:18.600
I've been to India six times.

00:21:18.600 --> 00:21:19.940
Okay, you bested me.

00:21:19.940 --> 00:21:23.250
Well, no, it's not a contest, but it kind of is, isn't

00:21:23.250 --> 00:21:23.520
it?

00:21:23.520 --> 00:21:25.740
Oh yeah, it's so funny talking about the trials.

00:21:25.740 --> 00:21:29.360
Everyone ought to go at least once to India.

00:21:29.360 --> 00:21:32.600
I think Bill Clinton once gave a speech at the Taj Mahal.

00:21:32.600 --> 00:21:35.320
He said, "There's two kinds of people in the world,

00:21:35.320 --> 00:21:37.180
people who have seen the Taj Mahal

00:21:37.180 --> 00:21:39.860
and people who have never seen the Taj Mahal."

00:21:39.860 --> 00:21:42.600
And North India is where it's at.

00:21:42.600 --> 00:21:47.100
This is the radically Hindu North,

00:21:47.100 --> 00:21:48.640
and that's where the red states are,

00:21:48.640 --> 00:21:51.020
and they're passing anti-conversion laws.

00:21:51.020 --> 00:21:53.420
There's a lot of persecution of Christians,

00:21:53.420 --> 00:21:58.420
but APII is going in humbly with food or with education.

00:21:58.420 --> 00:22:02.580
And eventually people do come to Christ

00:22:02.580 --> 00:22:05.740
'cause they see that we have some love to offer

00:22:05.740 --> 00:22:09.500
and everyone needs love.

00:22:09.500 --> 00:22:10.680
What is your experience,

00:22:10.680 --> 00:22:12.960
like when you're in the trenches ministering,

00:22:12.960 --> 00:22:14.520
what do you see?

00:22:14.520 --> 00:22:16.140
Yeah, it's a great question.

00:22:17.700 --> 00:22:19.040
One of the most obvious things

00:22:19.040 --> 00:22:20.740
is when you look into the eyes

00:22:20.740 --> 00:22:23.860
and you find hope for the first time in some people

00:22:23.860 --> 00:22:25.740
when they hear the gospel,

00:22:25.740 --> 00:22:29.180
you're dealing with a lot of impoverished communities.

00:22:29.180 --> 00:22:30.740
The Hindu faith is prevalent.

00:22:30.740 --> 00:22:33.180
And so a lot of the Hindu faith that we've experienced

00:22:33.180 --> 00:22:35.740
is people that have a hopelessness about it, right?

00:22:35.740 --> 00:22:36.580
The life that they have

00:22:36.580 --> 00:22:37.900
is the life that they've been designated.

00:22:37.900 --> 00:22:40.460
And because of the belief in the reincarnation,

00:22:40.460 --> 00:22:43.960
if you don't live it faithfully in that way, then...

00:22:43.960 --> 00:22:44.800
It's fatalism.

00:22:44.800 --> 00:22:46.460
You cannot change your destiny.

00:22:46.460 --> 00:22:47.300
Not at all.

00:22:47.300 --> 00:22:49.080
Because you sinned in a previous life,

00:22:49.080 --> 00:22:51.580
you came back in this life with poverty

00:22:51.580 --> 00:22:53.300
and it's your fault.

00:22:53.300 --> 00:22:54.660
We're not gonna help you.

00:22:54.660 --> 00:22:56.060
That's their attitude.

00:22:56.060 --> 00:22:58.100
But we come in with the opposite attitude

00:22:58.100 --> 00:23:00.540
that you are important to God,

00:23:00.540 --> 00:23:02.980
that God designed you in his image,

00:23:02.980 --> 00:23:05.840
that you're not being punished, but we can help you.

00:23:05.840 --> 00:23:08.860
And Jesus gives you a better future.

00:23:08.860 --> 00:23:10.140
Totally different message.

00:23:10.140 --> 00:23:11.320
Absolutely different message.

00:23:11.320 --> 00:23:12.420
And because of that,

00:23:12.420 --> 00:23:14.940
you go from hopelessness to hopefulness

00:23:14.940 --> 00:23:16.300
and they find out about Jesus.

00:23:16.300 --> 00:23:18.580
They find out that there is purpose in this world,

00:23:18.580 --> 00:23:20.140
that he designed them, he loves them,

00:23:20.140 --> 00:23:22.900
he sent Jesus for them and that changes everything.

00:23:22.900 --> 00:23:25.160
And so it's beautiful to see the eyes light up,

00:23:25.160 --> 00:23:27.500
the purpose moving forward.

00:23:27.500 --> 00:23:28.640
Then they bring their friends in

00:23:28.640 --> 00:23:30.140
and it transforms a community

00:23:30.140 --> 00:23:31.820
and it transforms their family.

00:23:31.820 --> 00:23:33.140
And then they move on to the next village

00:23:33.140 --> 00:23:34.980
and do the same thing and they replicate it,

00:23:34.980 --> 00:23:36.820
which is the DMM, the Discipleship Making Movement.

00:23:36.820 --> 00:23:41.620
You mentioned Discipleship Making Movement, DMM.

00:23:41.620 --> 00:23:44.980
This is like a house churches with Bible studies?

00:23:44.980 --> 00:23:46.940
Yeah, so what they do is,

00:23:46.940 --> 00:23:48.500
because of the anti-conversion laws,

00:23:48.500 --> 00:23:50.480
technically we don't convert anybody

00:23:50.480 --> 00:23:52.520
because what we're doing is just living in such a way

00:23:52.520 --> 00:23:53.940
that the gospel becomes attractive

00:23:53.940 --> 00:23:55.220
because the people are attracted

00:23:55.220 --> 00:23:56.340
because they're doing everything

00:23:56.340 --> 00:23:58.580
with just meeting needs in the community, right?

00:23:58.580 --> 00:24:01.500
And so what this eventually does is

00:24:01.500 --> 00:24:04.300
they get coming to a congregation,

00:24:04.300 --> 00:24:05.940
which is about a house fellowship

00:24:05.940 --> 00:24:07.860
of roughly 30 to 40 people.

00:24:07.860 --> 00:24:11.100
And they sit around with songs and praise to worship.

00:24:11.100 --> 00:24:12.820
They get their Bibles out.

00:24:12.820 --> 00:24:13.940
But a lot of our communities

00:24:13.940 --> 00:24:15.640
don't have Bibles translated yet.

00:24:15.640 --> 00:24:17.940
They have the languages roughly,

00:24:17.940 --> 00:24:18.960
but what we're noticing is

00:24:18.960 --> 00:24:21.280
there's so many different dialects of certain languages

00:24:21.280 --> 00:24:23.980
that it's not necessarily translating perfectly well.

00:24:23.980 --> 00:24:25.890
So there's a lot of organizations that we're working

00:24:25.890 --> 00:24:26.060
with

00:24:26.060 --> 00:24:27.900
to try and figure out, okay,

00:24:27.900 --> 00:24:29.620
how do we make this Bible make sense

00:24:29.620 --> 00:24:31.260
to the context in which they live?

00:24:31.260 --> 00:24:33.120
And so navigating some of that,

00:24:33.120 --> 00:24:35.020
so the chapters that we do have,

00:24:35.020 --> 00:24:36.460
we don't wait for the entire New Testament

00:24:36.460 --> 00:24:38.100
to be translated.

00:24:38.100 --> 00:24:39.980
Let's say we've got John 15 translated,

00:24:39.980 --> 00:24:43.030
which some CLCs, which is our community learning

00:24:43.030 --> 00:24:43.500
centers,

00:24:43.500 --> 00:24:46.100
some of them do have those Bibles translated.

00:24:46.100 --> 00:24:48.180
So they've got John 15 translated.

00:24:48.180 --> 00:24:50.480
Well, we're just gonna teach John 15 over and over

00:24:50.480 --> 00:24:50.820
again

00:24:50.820 --> 00:24:52.300
till we get John 16 next,

00:24:52.300 --> 00:24:53.140
till we get John 17.

00:24:53.140 --> 00:24:55.020
They don't even have the full gospel of John

00:24:55.020 --> 00:24:55.900
in their own language.

00:24:55.900 --> 00:24:56.780
Not yet.

00:24:56.780 --> 00:24:59.600
So what we do is they'll have an oratory, right?

00:24:59.600 --> 00:25:01.880
So then they have a memorization of it

00:25:01.880 --> 00:25:03.060
and they'll recite it to you

00:25:03.060 --> 00:25:04.740
because they've heard it so many times.

00:25:04.740 --> 00:25:06.860
So it's really this Bible memorization that's going on.

00:25:06.860 --> 00:25:07.940
It's pretty neat. Wow.

00:25:07.940 --> 00:25:10.300
Just imagine if there were translators

00:25:10.300 --> 00:25:13.160
who could put the entire New Testament in their

00:25:13.160 --> 00:25:13.780
language

00:25:13.780 --> 00:25:15.140
and even orally,

00:25:15.140 --> 00:25:18.180
'cause a lot of them are auditory learners

00:25:18.180 --> 00:25:20.700
and it's hard for them to read in English

00:25:20.700 --> 00:25:22.140
or in their own language.

00:25:22.140 --> 00:25:24.020
But once they hear the gospel,

00:25:24.020 --> 00:25:27.780
they hear the teachings of Jesus, they memorize it.

00:25:27.780 --> 00:25:30.820
They're so excited to share it with their friends.

00:25:30.820 --> 00:25:33.960
And that's how the DMM movement really has taken off

00:25:33.960 --> 00:25:34.900
all over India.

00:25:34.900 --> 00:25:37.100
Yes, it's a beautiful thing and a very humbling thing,

00:25:37.100 --> 00:25:39.820
especially being over here in America

00:25:39.820 --> 00:25:42.420
and then being able to open up your Bible freely,

00:25:42.420 --> 00:25:43.740
know what it says,

00:25:43.740 --> 00:25:45.320
and then knowing at the same time

00:25:45.320 --> 00:25:46.540
that I'm praying over my Bible,

00:25:46.540 --> 00:25:48.660
the people that are overseas there

00:25:48.660 --> 00:25:50.460
are receiving it in such a different way.

00:25:50.460 --> 00:25:52.800
It's beautiful.

00:25:52.800 --> 00:25:56.340
So discover how you can accelerate the movement.

